[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Exploring object writing in Java**\n\nI’m looking into how the private writeObject method in JournaledAlgorithm is invoked by ObjectOutputStream using reflection with the stream instance. It seems it also calls the final writeObject(byte[]). I wonder if coverage might need reflection metadata for the byte[]—but maybe it doesn’t? I'm puzzled about why it's uncovered after the test, so I’ll definitely need to investigate that further to understand what's happening.\n\n**Evaluating serialization concerns**\n\nI'm considering the ObjectOutputStream and its protected enableReplaceObject method. Should I replace the byte array representing the encoded JournaledAlgorithm? It feels risky since the serialization stream writes multiple byte arrays internally. The replaceObject method is specifically for objects serialized via writeObject, which makes me wonder if it's just our encoded byte array and not other objects. The outer JournaledAlgorithm fields are marked as transient, and I'm curious about class descriptors.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_09089e63592d3bce0169fbb7ef250c81a2821fcdcd8aa70b9f\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp-7gChKGCFxRYlAahfqYQ19sDvyOcD7-v1BcEmPJzagR2uxx0PI0-XZBnzROj6qD1X-dvMzw_Koepdn78Fu3Rh6s3HkioHZmPFjxvnuzf9WSFctIshnfc2jvYH6hrIegnNTk4m5ZSMxFexu5tfCYFiztbLJ0OQfWxmAHDT2fCLND4IXkQHXTrWrB4RI5byitDf84O59aVooVHOISRqRpP_cGkAL8qkN2Pr172RQrA0IbEApiGu1oaYjVL5fGv3KfRVD--DQCKDfJ1QUw1K7Vsk5QLPzLv8kHngvz0v-Pk4gbsfOvtdFt_Hjstb2HGzV2431-Bw583avD7_PEWowdmcEPDBmTD9JDCCtW61Hzw0mGUdfAP_H3BoIhFGzyPnihTPl1XDwfTrRmDFU1acLXVD8kblJBlFBv9f6TknT8E9acuK7N3GVsm8e4-mA-DL7jgF9Z9tDn_V8Y__JOn98frlv7MIoog-VVmx0bHsZvn_0es3v3VOi_aGzO08bz0C-9FAqbLeDEInEPp-CwdnrvWfLmrbuE0NEF0eGKkRg14IDD_jMvajMA2lALHWEzudRo9t7XUVo426IuVTtMdxaOKjnZThDJXakMo9fbqNlB7-KHjwuA1LQa3FbIN6COcrqVnAHgGJjxxqZmyscN3f02vDQmHHX1i0xe-iNq1J7e5JxVc2Zg4tXK2ZcVNQQwz03tzge3ZZexvcOhfr6dN3f