 custom `ObjectOutputStream` now replaces the first encoded `byte[]` written from `JournaledAlgorithm.writeObject(...)` with another `JournaledAlgorithm` instance.\n- The custom `ObjectInputStream` converts that nested `JournaledAlgorithm` back into the encoded `byte[]` expected by `JournaledAlgorithm.readObject(...)`.\n\nThis means the active class’s private serialization methods still complete normally, but their internal `out.writeObject(...)` and `in.readObject()` calls now process a Bouncy Castle object rather than only a primitive byte array payload, which should better exercise the remaining dynamic-access sites.\n\nTests were not run, per instruction.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_09089e63592d3bce0169fbb8fbb1dc81a2ab29634ef675fe43\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2174, "output": 720, "cacheRead": 43520, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 46414, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1778104560432, "responseId": "resp_09089e63592d3bce0169fbb8f1712481a289b490be8c78ab38"}, "toolResults": []}
